<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
The epithet 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">autralis</emphasis>
was selected based on the restricted distribution of this species in southern Argentina. It is not possible to use 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana patagonica" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a specific epithet in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because it is already in use in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana patagonica" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Speg. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alaria" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana australis" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the southernmost species of the genus. It shares with 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. foliosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">F. foliosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="F." lsidName="F. nana" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">F. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a similar habit forming dense cushions in dry, cold, and poor soils of Patagonian Argentina.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
